During a press conference in Paris, Vice President Kamala Harris discussed the productive nature of her trip to France and emphasized the enduring alliance between the United States and France. She highlighted the importance of global health, space exploration, regional security, the Indo-Pacific, inequality, technology, and democratic elections in the discussions she had with President Macron and other world leaders. Harris also addressed questions on inflation, vaccine passports, the recent elections in the United States, and jury discrimination in the trial of Ahmaud Arbery. She expressed frustration over the lack of paid family leave in the United States and the need for reforms to ensure representative juries. Harris commented on the crisis at the Polish-Belarus border and the hope for productive talks to reactivate the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) with Iran.